reviews.reviewText: He's 3 y.o. opened it and knew what to do immediately! It is a regular tablet too ( he downloaded YouTube!)He's happy.... makes Gramma happy!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Not the best
reviews.reviewText: I got this for my two-year-old. None of the functions would work. It seems like it was a return and then Resolved...I couldn't connect it to Wi-Fi. It said there was a parental block and that's why I couldn't connect it... But I never even got to that part. Because the settings screen would not stay on the screen. Long enough for me to do anything.Something that should have been simple was a headache.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Seems very cheap
reviews.reviewText: You get what you pay for. After a couple of days it wouldn't charge. Just stopped working. We purchased this cheap tablet for my youngest bcuz he wants my daughter's tablet. We didn't want to get anything too expensive bcuz he's only 1. The Amazon fire tablet my daughter has had for several years and never a problem. It's perfect for a child to toss around. I don't think this one is great for a child. We are keeping the replacement but I just know it's going to break again.
